wdi2-NY.ADJ.DNGY.CD.def: Energy depletion is the ratio of the value of the stock of energy resources to the remaining reserve lifetime. It covers coal, crude oil, and natural gas.
wdi2-NY.ADJ.DNGY.CD.name: Adjusted savings
wdi2-NY.ADJ.DNGY.CD.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.
